  • Field Details

    • ttime

      public long ttime
      Timestamp of the last executed tick

    • tick

      public long tick
      The counter which counts how many ticks have been executed so far. May wrap when Long.MAX_VALUE is reached and then starts counting from Long.MIN_VALUE again.

    • latestMspt

      public long latestMspt
      the amount of milliseconds it took to execute the last tick

    • tps

      public double tps
      The amount of ticks, executed every second, when the engine is running

    • started

      public boolean started
      if the engine is running

    • terminateOnError

      public boolean terminateOnError
      if the engine should terminate, when an uncaught exception occurs. This is false by default. therefore the engine will keep running no matter what.

    • tickables

      public java.util.Collection<Tickable> tickables
      list of Objects which are getting called every tick.

  • Method Details

    • loop

      public void loop()
      Main function of the Engine. Each loop, a new Tickthread is started, Afterwards it waits mspt milliseconds and terminates the thread afterwards. (Support for switching between lag and skipping may be implemented later) Prints error message, when errors occur during the loop, but does not terminate

    • tick

      public void tick()
      gets called every tick. calls all objects which are said to be executed

    • start

      public void start()
      starts the engine. !!can create multiple instances running at the same time!!

    • stop

      public void stop()
      stops the engine. Consider just removing the World from the engine instead. See World.stop() and/or World.switchWorld(World w)
